 development for school library enhancement. It aims at providing amazing topics, methodologies, approaches and experiences. It presents projects and practices addressing the challenges of supporting basic literacy, including contexts where many children cannot or do not access formal instruction on a regular basis. These may inspire education authorities, public librarians and other cultural professionals who work closely with schools and communities.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 4aSchulbibliotheken. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh1 aAdams, Tricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaffour-Awuah, Margaret, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBarrett, Helle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBastos, Glória, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBranch, Jennifer L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarmichael, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCombes, Barbara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConde, Elsa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aContassot, Maria Gunnarsson, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDas, Lourense H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDike, Virginia W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDoiron, Ray, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEriksson, Bibi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGallowaySolowan, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGroot, Joanne